&lt;p&gt;4DMT is a leading late-stage biotechnology company advancing durable and disease-targeted therapeutics with potential to transform treatment paradigms and provide unprecedented benefits to patients. The Company’s lead product candidate 4D-150 is designed to be a backbone therapy forming the foundation of treatment of blinding retinal vascular diseases by providing multi-year sustained delivery of anti-VEGF (aflibercept and anti-VEGF-C) with a single, safe, intravitreal injection, which substantially reduces the treatment burden associated with current bolus injections. The Company’s lead indication for 4D-150 is wet age-related macular degeneration, which is currently in Phase 3 development, and second indication is diabetic macular edema. The Company’s second product candidate is 4D-710, which is the first known genetic medicine to demonstrate successful delivery and expression of the CFTR transgene in the lungs of people with cystic fibrosis after aerosol delivery&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;GENERAL SUMMARY:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4DMT needs a motivated, collaborative, and experienced Administrative Assistant (Contract). The primary function of this is provide direct administrative support to senior executives within the organization with a strong focus on calendar management, monthly expense reporting, processing of financial requisitions consulting contracting and other internal business processes within the business as needed. The role will report directly to the Executive Business Partner. This is a hybrid position, with in-office days arranged according to business needs and determined by the hiring manager (minimum 3 days onsite).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES: &lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;ADMINISTRATIVE SUPPORT FUNCTIONS&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct Support for Senior Executives:&lt;/strong&gt; Accountability to manage administrative tasks with a high priority focus on calendar management, supporting schedule changes, managing multiple incoming requests for meetings, working in alignment with the weekly priorities of each executive.&amp;nbsp; Includes tasks to support project teams as needed with logistics relating to key business meetings as directed by hiring manager and assigned executives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calendar Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Scheduling and editing of meetings and appointments, setting up Zoom video conferences, assigning delegate rights as directed. Manage bookings for single and recurring meetings, collaborating with other members of the administrative team in arranging schedules to best accommodate attendee calendar conflicts or time sensitive, high-priority meetings. Must have the ability to be flexible and provide prompt real-time response to changing business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meeting Logistics and Planning: &lt;/strong&gt;Book conference rooms, coordinate attendee confirmations when needed, manage room set-up and catering, when needed, be on site to receive food deliveries and set up conference rooms. Support planning and coordination of offsite meetings and employee events by completing specific tasks, including but not limited to sourcing vendors, comparing options, performing basic cost analysis and communication with vendors regarding lodging and meals needs and ground transportation details, purchasing of gifts and supplies

